            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.24442/2605.24442v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Composed Image Retrieval for applied Earth Observation.We illustrate how composed queries (query image+query text)\nenable controllable retrieval by specifying a targeted change.\n(a) Activity monitoring: a parking-lot query image composed withbeing emptyretrieves visuallysimilarparking areas with low vehicle occupancy.\n(b) Capacity monitoring: A facility query image composed withhaving fourretrieves visuallysimilarsites exhibiting a different quantity attribute.\n(c) Disaster monitoring: a pre-event query image composed withpost-fireretrieves post-event imagery of thesamescene consistent with wildfire impact.\n(d) Urban development: a pre-construction query image composed withnew buildingsretrieves thesamescene exhibiting recent construction.\nFor each query, retrieved candidates (ranked left-to-right, top-to-bottom) are produced by FreeDom[19]with OpenAI CLIP[67];greenborders indicate correct retrievals under the respective evaluation criterion (a,b: same class + target attribute value, c,d: same scene + target change), whileredborders indicate mismatches.\nImages in (a,b) are from PatternNet[112], (c) from xView2[41], and (d) from LEVIR-CC[50].",
                "position": 367
            }
        ]
    },
